Our #1 requested feature is finally here! TrapCall now automatically blocks calls from spammers and numbers in your blacklist, so your phone will never ring with another unwanted call. Simply turn on Call Blocking on your iPhone with our instructions in the app and you'll be protected from over 100,000 known spammers!

• TrapCall's new spam call blocking will automatically block over 100,000 known spammers, telemarketers and robocallers from being able to ring to your phone
• TrapCall will now block any numbers in your blacklist from being able to ring your phone
• Spammers that are blocked by the app will hear a message that your number has been disconnected, so they will stop calling, and won't be able to leave you a voicemail!
• Our Global Spam List is continuously updated and sent to your phone throughout the day without you needing to manually update anything!
• If a spam caller slips through, simply add their number to your blacklist and they'll be blocked for good. We'll also use this data to help detect spam numbers and improve our Global Spam List for other TrapCall users
• Our new Whitelist feature ensures that you can add numbers you want to allow to always ring to your phone
• iOS 10.1 or later is required to enable TrapCall's new spam call blocking

If you need help enabling Spam Call Blocking on your iPhone:
- Open the iPhone Settings app
- Scroll down and tap "Phone"
- Then tap "Call Blocking & Identification"
- Tap the button next to "TrapCall" so it turns green

If you run into any issues, please don't hesitate to contact our support via the app or our website! We think you're going to love TrapCall even more with our new call blocking!
